  "texts": [
    "Although Dewey's theory intends to explain human moral development and current value alignment claims similarly expect LLMs to learn human morality, LLMs are ultimately different from humans in their lack of self-awareness.",
    "Therefore, we also seek to explore whether employing Dewey's theory to the moral development of LLMs can help reveal the limitations inherent in the current value alignment approach.",
    "To evaluate the explanatory power of Dewey's moral philosophy in enhancing LLMs' moral competence, we assess LLMs in the context of moral growth (Dewey's theory of moral development) by establishing two experimental stages centered around the beating scenario, which involves one individual physically attacking another.",
    "This scenario was selected due to its universal condemnation as immoral across cultures and religions.",
    "The first stage evaluates the performance of LLMs (GPT-2, GPT-3, and ChatGPT) in making moral judgments on fundamental questions, while the second stage appraises the advancement of LLMs (ChatGPT, ERNIE Bot, and ChatGLM) in exhibiting moral behavior and solving complex moral dilemmas."
  ],
